            "id": "4451479",
            "title": "Atour Lifestyle Holdings Non-GAAP EPS of $0.11, revenue of $262.63M beats by $2.4M",
            "description": "<html><body><ul>\n<li>Atour Lifestyle Holdings <a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/pr/20113077-atour-lifestyle-holdings-limited-reports-first-quarter-of-2025-unaudited-financial-results\">press release</a>  (<span class=\"ticker-hover-wrapper\">NASDAQ:<a href=\"https://seekingalpha.com/symbol/ATAT\" title=\"Atour Lifestyle Holdings Limited\">ATAT</a></span>): Q1  Non-GAAP EPS of $0.11.</li>\n<li>Revenue of $262.63M <font color=\"green\"> beats by $2.4M</font>.</li>\n<li>As of March 31, 2025, there were 1,727 hotels with a total of 194,559 hotel rooms in operation across Atour’s hotel network, representing rapid increases of 32.6% and 31.3% year-over-year in terms of the number of hotels and hotel rooms, respectively.</li>\n<li>As of March 31, 2025, there were 755 manachised hotels under development in our pipeline. The average daily room rate (“ADR”) was RMB418 for the first quarter of 2025, compared with RMB430 for the same period of 2024 and RMB420 for the previous quarter.</li>\n<li>The occupancy rate was 70.2% for the first quarter of 2025, compared with 73.3% for the same period of 2024 and 77.0% for the previous quarter.</li>\n<li>The revenue per available room (“RevPAR”) was RMB304 for the first quarter of 2025, compared with RMB328 for the same period of 2024 and RMB337 for the previous quarter.</li>\n<li>For the full year of 2025, the Company currently expects total net revenues to increase by 25% to 30% compared with the full year of 2024.</li>\n</ul>\n</body></html>",
            "image": "https://static.seekingalpha.com/assets/og_image_1200-29b2bfe1a595477db6826bd2126c63ac2091efb7ec76347a8e7f81ba17e3de6c.png",
